## News and awards {.central}

[[2024]{.blue}] I will travel to Madagascar for the [annual meeting]{.blue} of [LIFEPLAN](https://cordis.europa.eu/project/id/856506) (a planetary inventory of life), funded by an [ERC Synergy Grant]{.blue} focusing on global biodiversity research.

[[2024]{.blue}] [Daniele Durante](https://danieledurante.github.io/web/) was awarded an [ERC Starting Grant]{.blue} for the project [NEMESIS](https://danieledurante.github.io/web/nemesis.html), focusing on the sociogenesis of criminal networks. I am very happy to be involved in the research group!

[[2022]{.blue}] [National Scientific Qualification for Associate Professor in Statistics (13/D1)]{.blue}. 

[[2021]{.blue}] [Young Talents Award 2021]{.blue}. University of Milano-Bicocca, Accademia Nazionale dei Lincei. [[Award](https://www.unimib.it/sites/default/files/GT_2021_Vincitori_1.pdf)]

[[2020]{.blue}] [Savage Award 2020 (Theory and Methods)]{.blue}. American Statistical Association (ASA), International Society for Bayesian Analysis (ISBA). [[Award](https://bayesian.org/project/savage-award/)] [[News](https://bidsa.unibocconi.eu/newsevents/tommaso-rigon-awarded-his-phd-dissertation)]

[[2016]{.blue}] [Best Ph.D. student in Statistics]{.blue}, Bocconi University, Academic Year 2016/2017 (09/2017).

